<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-05-09T15:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-05-09T15:36:00-05:00" n="596" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d596">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">412.00/99: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Summerlin</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-05-09T14:00:00-06:36"><hi rend="italic">May 9,
                                            1919, 2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[<hi rend="italic">Received
                                        May 10, 2.10 a.m.</hi>]</dateline></opener>
                            <p>2081. Secretary of Mexican Claims Commission today stated that the
                                total amount of claims presented as mentioned in Embassy’s telegram
                                2065 April 26, 2 p.m. included only claims presented to the
                                commission now in session, but that claims to the extent of
                                approximately 43,000,000 pesos had been presented to the former
                                claims commission<note n="18" xml:id="d596fn18">Established June 30,
                                    1911; see <ref target="frus1912#pg_934"><hi rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>, 1912, pp. 934</ref> ff.</note>
                                <pb facs="0721" n="636" xml:id="pg_636"/> for damages suffered
                                during the Madero revolution and that all these claims have been
                                taken over by the new commission.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Summerlin</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>